{
    "analysis": "From prior steps: metric.csv and log.csv overlap the incident window (data from 2024-01-19 03:50—04:14 UTC). trace.csv and error_logs.csv are empty. Metric analysis highlighted strong relative latency increases for the orders service (orders latency-50 breach_ratio ~6.6 and latency-90 ~2.1) with earliest anomaly ~2024-01-19 03:52:00 UTC. Many services show log.error_count anomalies, but those are driven by p95==0 and in-window zeros (not informative). log.row_count shows only small increases around 03:58. The most significant and actionable signal so far is the orders latency spike starting ~03:52. We now need to confirm whether orders' resource KPIs (cpu, mem, socket, diskio) also show faults (which would indicate resource exhaustion like high CPU/memory/disk I/O) or whether the issue is isolated to latency (pointing to network latency or downstream socket issues). To decide between resource exhaustion vs network/socket latency, we must inspect orders' per-KPI anomaly segments (consecutive anomalies) and resource KPI breach ratios in the incident window.",
